Joyce Cox was strangled to death on her way home from school in Cardiff on September 28, 1939 . 
  Her body was found dumped by a railway station but her killer has never been caught . 
  Her cousin Terry Phillips has accused police of a 'cover-up' after they ordered that the case file be kept secret until 2040 . 
  Met Police said information could not be released because it was unfair to the mystery suspect . 
  Joyce was just days away from her fifth birthday when she was killed . 
 